# Whisky Hikes Freezed Configuration Guide

## Overview
Diese Regel beschreibt die korrekte Konfiguration von Freezed 3.x für das Whisky Hikes Projekt und löst häufige Probleme bei der Code-Generierung.

## Freezed 3.x Requirements

### 1. Class Definition
**WICHTIG**: Alle Freezed-Modelle müssen als `abstract class` definiert werden:

```dart
// ✅ KORREKT - Freezed 3.x
@freezed
abstract class Company with _$Company {
  const factory Company({
    required String id,
    required String name,
    String? description,
  }) = _Company;

  factory Company.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$CompanyFromJson(json);
}

// ❌ FALSCH - Funktioniert nicht mit Freezed 3.x
@freezed
class Company with _$Company { ... }  // Fehlt 'abstract'

// ❌ FALSCH - Funktioniert nicht mit Freezed 3.x
sealed class Company with _$Company { ... }  // Falscher Ansatz
```

### 2. Required Annotations
```dart
import 'package:freezed_annotation/freezed_annotation.dart';

part 'company.freezed.dart';  // Freezed-Generierung
part 'company.g.dart';        // JSON-Serialisierung
```

## Code Generation Workflow

### 1. Build Runner Commands
```bash
# Vollständige Generierung (empfohlen)
flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs

# Nur Freezed generieren
flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs --build-filter=freezed

# Nur JSON-Serialisierung generieren
flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs --build-filter=json_serializable

# Nur Mocks generieren
flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs --build-filter=mockito
```

### 2. Watch Mode für Entwicklung
```bash
# Überwacht Datei-Änderungen und generiert automatisch
flutter pub run build_runner watch
```

### 3. Clean Build
```bash
# Bei Problemen: Alles löschen und neu generieren
flutter clean
flutter pub get
flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
```

## Common Freezed Patterns

### 1. Basic Model
```dart
@freezed
abstract class Hike with _$Hike {
  const factory Hike({
    required int id,
    required String name,
    required double length,
    required double steep,
    required int elevation,
    String? description,
    String? thumbnailImageUrl,
    @Default(false) bool isFavorite,
  }) = _Hike;

  factory Hike.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$HikeFromJson(json);
}
```

### 2. Model mit Enums
```dart
enum Difficulty { easy, mid, hard, veryHard }

@freezed
abstract class Hike with _$Hike {
  const factory Hike({
    required int id,
    required String name,
    required Difficulty difficulty,
    @Default(Difficulty.mid) Difficulty defaultDifficulty,
  }) = _Hike;

  factory Hike.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$HikeFromJson(json);
}
```

### 3. Model mit Custom JSON Keys
```dart
@freezed
abstract class Profile with _$Profile {
  const factory Profile({
    required String id,
    @JsonKey(name: 'first_name') required String firstName,
    @JsonKey(name: 'last_name') required String lastName,
    @JsonKey(name: 'date_of_birth') DateTime? dateOfBirth,
    @JsonKey(name: 'image_url') String imageUrl,
  }) = _Profile;

  factory Profile.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$ProfileFromJson(json);
}
```

### 4. Model mit Computed Properties
```dart
@freezed
abstract class Company with _$Company {
  const factory Company({
    required String id,
    required String name,
    required String countryCode,
    required String city,
  }) = _Company;

  factory Company.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$CompanyFromJson(json);
}

// Extension für computed properties
extension CompanyExtensions on Company {
  bool get isDachAddress => ['DE', 'AT', 'CH'].contains(countryCode);
  
  String get displayAddress => '$city, $countryCode';
}
```

## JSON Serialization

### 1. Custom Converters
```dart
class DateTimeConverter implements JsonConverter<DateTime, String> {
  const DateTimeConverter();

  @override
  DateTime fromJson(String json) => DateTime.parse(json);

  @override
  String toJson(DateTime object) => object.toIso8601String();
}

@freezed
abstract class Event with _$Event {
  const factory Event({
    required String id,
    @DateTimeConverter() required DateTime startTime,
    @DateTimeConverter() required DateTime endTime,
  }) = _Event;

  factory Event.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$EventFromJson(json);
}
```

### 2. Nullable vs Non-Nullable Fields
```dart
@freezed
abstract class User with _$User {
  const factory User({
    required String id,           // Non-nullable
    required String email,        // Non-nullable
    String? firstName,           // Nullable
    String? lastName,            // Nullable
    @Default('en') String locale, // Mit Default-Wert
  }) = _User;

  factory User.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$UserFromJson(json);
}
```

## Troubleshooting

### 1. Common Compilation Errors

#### "Missing implementations for these members"
**Problem**: Klasse ist nicht als `abstract` definiert
**Lösung**: `abstract class` verwenden

#### "Could not generate toJson code for type"
**Problem**: Typ kann nicht serialisiert werden
**Lösung**: `JsonConverter` oder `JsonKey` mit `fromJson`/`toJson` verwenden

#### "Target of URI doesn't exist"
**Problem**: Generierte Dateien fehlen
**Lösung**: `build_runner` ausführen

### 2. Generation Issues

#### Freezed generiert nicht
```bash
# Dependencies prüfen
flutter pub deps

# Build Runner neu installieren
flutter pub run build_runner clean
flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
```

#### JSON-Serialisierung funktioniert nicht
```bash
# Nur JSON-Serialisierung neu generieren
flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs --build-filter=json_serializable
```

### 3. Version Compatibility
```yaml
# pubspec.yaml - Kompatible Versionen
dependencies:
  freezed_annotation: ^3.1.0

dev_dependencies:
  build_runner: ^2.7.0
  freezed: ^3.2.0
  json_serializable: ^6.10.0
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Model Organization
```dart
// lib/domain/models/hike.dart
import 'package:freezed_annotation/freezed_annotation.dart';

part 'hike.freezed.dart';
part 'hike.g.dart';

@freezed
abstract class Hike with _$Hike {
  const factory Hike({...}) = _Hike;
  factory Hike.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$HikeFromJson(json);
}

// Extension in derselben Datei
extension HikeExtensions on Hike {
  // Business Logic hier
}
```

### 2. Import Management
```dart
// Immer relative Imports für part-Dateien
part 'hike.freezed.dart';  // ✅
part 'hike.g.dart';        // ✅

// Nie absolute Imports für part-Dateien
part 'package:whisky_hikes/domain/models/hike.freezed.dart';  // ❌
```

### 3. Testing mit Freezed
```dart
// test/domain/models/hike_test.dart
void main() {
  group('Hike Model Tests', () {
    test('should create hike with required fields', () {
      final hike = Hike(
        id: 1,
        name: 'Test Hike',
        length: 5.0,
        steep: 0.3,
        elevation: 200,
      );
      
      expect(hike.id, equals(1));
      expect(hike.name, equals('Test Hike'));
    });
    
    test('should serialize to JSON', () {
      final hike = Hike(
        id: 1,
        name: 'Test Hike',
        length: 5.0,
        steep: 0.3,
        elevation: 200,
      );
      
      final json = hike.toJson();
      expect(json['id'], equals(1));
      expect(json['name'], equals('Test Hike'));
    });
  });
}
```

## Migration von Freezed 2.x

### 1. Breaking Changes
- `class` → `abstract class`
- Neue Annotation-Syntax
- Geänderte Code-Generierung

### 2. Migration Steps
```bash
# 1. Dependencies aktualisieren
flutter pub upgrade --major-versions

# 2. Code anpassen (abstract class hinzufügen)
# 3. Build Runner ausführen
flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs

# 4. Tests ausführen
flutter test
```

